  "body": "### Describe the feature\n\nI'd like to be able to set the blocknumber and timestamp inside of my `hardhat.config` file for the local hardhat network. You can achieve this easily on a forked network:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nnetworks: {\r\n    hardhat: {\r\n      blockConfirmations: 1,\r\n      forking: {\r\n        url: process.env.FORKING_URL,\r\n        blockNumber: 17372500,\r\n      },\r\n    },\r\n```\r\n\r\nBut if I wanted to set the block number on my local network, it doesn't work or give the user any warning/error message:\r\n\r\n```js\r\n networks: {\r\n    hardhat: {\r\n      blockConfirmations: 1,\r\n      blockNumber: 17372500,\r\n    },\r\n  },\r\n```\r\n\r\nFor additional customization and specific use-cases such as [this one](https://ethereum.stackexchange.com/questions/154731/is-it-possible-to-set-a-custom-start-time-and-block-number-for-a-local-hardhat-n),  it would be helpful to set these values inside the config.\n\n### Search terms\n\nhardhat node block number",
